WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.243 --> 00:00:10.939
(KITCHENWARE CLATTERING)

2
00:00:14.481 --> 00:00:17.474
Morning. Dad. I made you some
of your favorite banana-nut muffins.

3
00:00:17.551 --> 00:00:21.989
Oh. yeah? Trying to get un-grounded
before <i>Robocop</i> comes out on Friday?

4
00:00:22.089 --> 00:00:24.786
Did I mention I made
them all by myself?

5
00:00:24.858 --> 00:00:27.794
Mmm. Not bad. What
recipe did you use?

6
00:00:28.362 --> 00:00:34.097
My recipe? I can't tell
you that. It's a secret.

7
00:00:34.201 --> 00:00:37.180
Oh. well. let me see if I can guess some
of the ingredients that you put in here.

8
00:00:37.204 --> 00:00:40.470
Is that a hint of
cinnamon that I'm tasting?

9
00:00:40.541 --> 00:00:42.271
Oh. yeah. just a
little hint. Mmm-hmm.

10
00:00:42.342 --> 00:00:46.279
And I'm detecting
just a touch of cilantro

11
00:00:47.481 --> 00:00:49.006
and thyme. Am I right?

12
00:00:49.082 --> 00:00:51.244
Whoa. Dad. you're really sharp.

13
00:00:51.318 --> 00:00:52.616
Yeah. I am.

14
00:00:52.686 --> 00:00:56.054
Gus. you wanna
come out of the pantry?

15
00:01:01.929 --> 00:01:04.797
(SIGHING) Shawn. what have
I told you 1.000 times before?

16
00:01:04.865 --> 00:01:06.766
(SIGHS) Don't hide
Gus in the pantry?

17
00:01:06.833 --> 00:01:10.964
No. "A lie always
leads to more lies."

18
00:01:11.038 --> 00:01:12.849
Instead of lying to me
about baking these yourself

19
00:01:12.873 --> 00:01:15.968
and then lying to me about your
secret ingredients that you put in.

20
00:01:16.043 --> 00:01:18.123
you should've just said that
Gus baked these muffins.

21
00:01:18.178 --> 00:01:20.374
and I might've let
you off the hook.

22
00:01:20.447 --> 00:01:22.643
Who said Gus made
them? Go to your room.

23
00:01:22.716 --> 00:01:24.548
I don't know where
that is. Shawn.

24
00:01:24.618 --> 00:01:26.450
Who's Shawn?

25
00:01:32.593 --> 00:01:34.585
Public parking. huh?

26
00:01:34.661 --> 00:01:37.130
Well. nice to know that my
first visit to Santa Barbara

27
00:01:37.197 --> 00:01:40.565
isn't a good enough reason for you to pop
for a couple of extra bucks for the valet.

28
00:01:40.634 --> 00:01:42.745
The restaurant doesn't have
valet parking. Uncle Burton.

29
00:01:42.769 --> 00:01:45.000
Am I gonna need tokens
to use the bathroom?

30
00:01:45.072 --> 00:01:46.938
It's been well reviewed.
It got four spoons.

31
00:01:47.007 --> 00:01:48.669
Crack spoons
from the sound of it.

32
00:01:48.742 --> 00:01:50.210
Gus! Wait up!

33
00:01:50.277 --> 00:01:51.609
Shawn?

34
00:01:51.845 --> 00:01:52.938
Finally.

35
00:01:53.013 --> 00:01:54.709
You know. I went to
two comic book stores

36
00:01:54.781 --> 00:01:57.148
and three women's volleyball
games looking for you.

37
00:01:57.217 --> 00:01:58.981
Luckily. your phone has GPS.

38
00:01:59.052 --> 00:02:00.953
You tracked me? Yes. I did.

39
00:02:01.021 --> 00:02:03.889
With a little help from my friends
at your wireless service provider.

40
00:02:03.957 --> 00:02:07.826
By the way. they might be calling.
They think you're a fugitive from justice.

41
00:02:07.894 --> 00:02:09.385
Run with it.

42
00:02:09.463 --> 00:02:11.125
Who is this. Burton?
Shawn Spencer.

43
00:02:11.198 --> 00:02:13.667
He knows who you are. He
knows what you do. Don't speak.

44
00:02:13.734 --> 00:02:15.532
We're going to dinner.
You're not invited.

45
00:02:15.602 --> 00:02:16.900
Let's roll. Uncle Burton.

46
00:02:16.970 --> 00:02:19.997
Uh. Jules just called. We
got a case. We should go.

47
00:02:20.073 --> 00:02:23.669
You know. Shawn. maybe you
should handle this one yourself.

48
00:02:23.744 --> 00:02:25.337
There's a first
time for everything.

49
00:02:25.412 --> 00:02:27.574
First time for... What
are you talking about?

50
00:02:27.648 --> 00:02:31.085
Sorry. Shawn. I can't make it.

51
00:02:31.151 --> 00:02:34.383
Oh. for crying out loud. Burton.
the cops are handing you a case.

52
00:02:34.454 --> 00:02:37.822
You gotta take it. You're the
only psychic detective they've got.

53
00:02:37.891 --> 00:02:40.053
That's very funny. Don't speak.

54
00:02:40.127 --> 00:02:42.323
Just one minute. Yeah.

55
00:02:42.396 --> 00:02:45.855
I know what you're thinking. Of course
you do. You're a psychic detective.

56
00:02:45.999 --> 00:02:48.199
A few months ago. I was on
the phone with my great-aunt.

57
00:02:48.235 --> 00:02:50.932
who's hard of hearing and
pretty much out of it in general.

58
00:02:51.004 --> 00:02:55.203
I told her I was working part-time
at a psychic detective agency.

59
00:02:55.709 --> 00:02:58.888
She must have misunderstood. because now
everybody on my mom's side of the family

60
00:02:58.912 --> 00:03:01.040
thinks that I'm a
psychic detective

61
00:03:01.114 --> 00:03:03.583
and that you're... No. Gay?

62
00:03:03.650 --> 00:03:04.674
German? No.

63
00:03:04.751 --> 00:03:06.014
Invisible? My assistant. Shawn.

64
00:03:06.086 --> 00:03:10.490
Wow. Gus. this is... Wow.

65
00:03:10.557 --> 00:03:12.321
I know. It's a mess.

66
00:03:12.426 --> 00:03:14.370
Why don't you just tell them it
was a simple misunderstanding?

67
00:03:14.394 --> 00:03:15.394
It's too late.

68
00:03:15.462 --> 00:03:16.555
I can't come clean now

69
00:03:16.630 --> 00:03:19.008
without everyone thinking that
I lied to them in the first place.

70
00:03:19.032 --> 00:03:23.128
Plus. Uncle Burton has had it out for
me ever since I started going by "Gus."

71
00:03:23.203 --> 00:03:26.196
even though I'm named after him.
If he figures out that I'm not psychic.

72
00:03:26.273 --> 00:03:28.384
he's gonna make it his mission to
destroy me in front of everybody.

73
00:03:28.408 --> 00:03:31.674
All right. say no more. You're
not getting destroyed by that man.

74
00:03:31.745 --> 00:03:33.714
UNCLE BURTON: I'm
getting hungry over here.

75
00:03:33.780 --> 00:03:35.749
Don't worry. I have a plan.

76
00:03:35.816 --> 00:03:36.943
You do?

77
00:03:37.017 --> 00:03:38.610
Uncle Burton! Mmm?

78
00:03:38.685 --> 00:03:43.623
How would you like to come with
us and watch your nephew in action?

79
00:03:43.857 --> 00:03:47.453
Tag along with you guys on
a real detective case? Yeah.

80
00:03:47.527 --> 00:03:50.463
Hey. maybe this won't be the most
boring vacation in the world after all.

81
00:03:50.530 --> 00:03:51.657
(ALL LAUGHING)

82
00:03:51.732 --> 00:03:52.893
Maybe.

83
00:03:54.034 --> 00:03:57.527
I can't wait to watch you
work your psychic magic.

84
00:04:02.943 --> 00:04:06.505
<i>I know. you know That
I'm not telling the truth</i>

85
00:04:06.580 --> 00:04:09.641
<i>I know. you know They
just don't have any proof</i>

86
00:04:09.716 --> 00:04:12.880
<i>Embrace the deception
Learn how to bend</i>

87
00:04:12.953 --> 00:04:17.118
<i>Your worst inhibitions tend
to psych you out in the end</i>

88
00:04:24.464 --> 00:04:26.023
(CAMERA CLICKING)

89
00:04:26.666 --> 00:04:28.760
So. how you feeling.
buddy? A little nervous?

90
00:04:28.835 --> 00:04:30.463
Little something
happening in the belly?

91
00:04:30.537 --> 00:04:32.972
Maybe you should do some
of your Lamaze breathing.

92
00:04:33.039 --> 00:04:34.701
No. You know why. Shawn?

93
00:04:34.775 --> 00:04:37.056
Because your little plan to
embarrass me isn't gonna work.

94
00:04:37.110 --> 00:04:39.272
As soon as the cops see
Uncle Burton hanging around.

95
00:04:39.346 --> 00:04:40.939
they're gonna
kick him right out.

96
00:04:41.014 --> 00:04:43.347
Nice try. Shawny boy!

97
00:04:43.416 --> 00:04:44.416
Hey. guys.

98
00:04:44.484 --> 00:04:45.645
Ah. Buzz.

99
00:04:45.719 --> 00:04:48.780
You know. I'm not sure they're gonna
want you having any guests in here.

100
00:04:48.855 --> 00:04:50.619
I mean. since it's a
crime scene and all.

101
00:04:50.690 --> 00:04:52.215
No. it's not. It's not?

102
00:04:52.292 --> 00:04:55.751
No. There's no crime
scene tape at the door.

103
00:04:55.829 --> 00:04:58.663
the forensic guys are not
collecting any evidence.

104
00:04:58.732 --> 00:05:00.877
and it seems as though you
guys don't suspect foul play.

105
00:05:00.901 --> 00:05:03.166
So I've got as much
right to be here as you do.

106
00:05:03.236 --> 00:05:06.673
And don't give me any of
that fancy police talk. please.

107
00:05:06.807 --> 00:05:10.266
I've seen enough <i>Hill Street
Blues</i> to know what's what.

108
00:05:11.444 --> 00:05:12.969
I gotta go. Mmm.

109
00:05:15.415 --> 00:05:17.907
Hey. thanks for coming so quick.

110
00:05:17.984 --> 00:05:20.715
Who's this? This is my
Uncle Burton from New Jersey.

111
00:05:20.787 --> 00:05:22.221
Shawn invited him.

112
00:05:22.289 --> 00:05:24.485
Very nice to meet
you. Uncle Burton?

113
00:05:24.558 --> 00:05:27.687
His mother named him after
me. It's not a very common name.

114
00:05:27.761 --> 00:05:30.890
but some of us
still use it proudly.

115
00:05:31.164 --> 00:05:33.861
Jules. what's the
skinny? What do you got?

116
00:05:33.934 --> 00:05:37.132
Vince Wagner. longtime restaurant
critic at the <i>Santa Barbara Mirror.</i>

117
00:05:37.204 --> 00:05:40.265
dies suddenly after eating
his wife's chicken soup.

118
00:05:40.340 --> 00:05:42.002
All signs point
to natural causes.

119
00:05:42.075 --> 00:05:44.840
but the wife's acting
a little suspicious.

120
00:05:44.911 --> 00:05:46.322
I want to make sure
I didn't miss anything.

121
00:05:46.346 --> 00:05:48.144
so I'd like for you to
get a reading on her.

122
00:05:48.215 --> 00:05:50.275
Then that's what we will do.

123
00:05:50.350 --> 00:05:51.818
She's in the den.

124
00:05:53.687 --> 00:05:57.283
Finally. A chance to see
Gus's psychic powers at work.

125
00:05:57.357 --> 00:05:59.326
Shawn. can I speak
to you for a second?

126
00:05:59.392 --> 00:06:00.826
What is the problem here?

127
00:06:00.894 --> 00:06:03.105
Stop playing. Shawn. You
know I can't do this. Yes. you can.

128
00:06:03.129 --> 00:06:05.826
No. I can't. You make some
observations. you form a conclusion

129
00:06:05.899 --> 00:06:08.277
and you reveal it to everybody in
a ridiculous and or roundabout way.

130
00:06:08.301 --> 00:06:09.941
What are you talking
about? I'll show you.

131
00:06:09.970 --> 00:06:11.666
What?

132
00:06:11.738 --> 00:06:14.401
Uh-huh. Whoa.

133
00:06:14.474 --> 00:06:15.840
Oh!

134
00:06:22.349 --> 00:06:24.318
Raw chicken next to
vegetables. charred pots.

135
00:06:24.384 --> 00:06:26.080
a refrigerator full of
takeout containers.

136
00:06:26.152 --> 00:06:27.780
What does that tell
you about the wife?

137
00:06:27.888 --> 00:06:31.120
I don't know. She sucks at
cooking. Oh. you're on fire.

138
00:06:31.191 --> 00:06:33.285
What? Uncle Burton.
come quick! It's happening!

139
00:06:33.360 --> 00:06:35.727
Shawn. stop this. Stop playing.
Put your hand to your head.

140
00:06:35.795 --> 00:06:38.390
It really helps sell the
thing. I'm not doing it. Shawn.

141
00:06:38.465 --> 00:06:40.127
This better be worth
skipping dinner for.

142
00:06:40.200 --> 00:06:42.863
He's a psychic wildebeest.

143
00:06:43.536 --> 00:06:46.700
(STAMMERING)
I'm seeing something.

144
00:06:48.541 --> 00:06:51.010
I'm sensing something.

145
00:06:51.077 --> 00:06:52.511
(PROMPTING)

146
00:06:52.579 --> 00:06:54.309
I'm tasting something.

147
00:06:54.848 --> 00:06:56.783
Ugh.

148
00:06:57.517 --> 00:06:58.951
It tastes bad.

149
00:06:59.786 --> 00:07:01.277
She's a bad cook!

150
00:07:01.354 --> 00:07:03.721
MRS. WAGNER: Huh! You
sound just like my husband.

151
00:07:05.825 --> 00:07:08.852
Mrs. Wagner? Oh.
please. excuse my partner.

152
00:07:08.929 --> 00:07:12.764
His psychic visions are
often terribly impolite.

153
00:07:12.832 --> 00:07:17.532
No need to apologize. I
really am a terrible cook.

154
00:07:17.604 --> 00:07:19.698
I'm very sorry for your loss.

155
00:07:19.773 --> 00:07:23.505
I'm sensing that you're at peace
with your husband's passing.

156
00:07:23.944 --> 00:07:30.282
Well. not exactly at peace. But it
wasn't easy being married to a food critic.

157
00:07:30.350 --> 00:07:32.342
He rated everything I did.

158
00:07:32.419 --> 00:07:34.718
Surely he couldn't
have rated everything.

159
00:07:34.788 --> 00:07:35.788
(CHUCKLES)

160
00:07:38.224 --> 00:07:40.250
I never broke two stars.

161
00:07:41.528 --> 00:07:44.862
Well. that's awfully harsh.

162
00:07:44.931 --> 00:07:47.628
So why did you keep
on cooking for him?

163
00:07:48.101 --> 00:07:52.630
Health reasons. He had gotten a
worrisome checkup from his doctor recently.

164
00:07:52.706 --> 00:07:56.871
He ate out everyday for his job and
always brought the leftovers home.

165
00:07:56.943 --> 00:08:01.506
So I started making him healthy.
home-cooked meals just once a week.

166
00:08:01.581 --> 00:08:03.914
That's what dinner was tonight.

167
00:08:03.984 --> 00:08:05.976
Thank you for your
time. Mrs. Wagner.

168
00:08:06.052 --> 00:08:08.214
You have our condolences.

169
00:08:09.055 --> 00:08:11.047
(SIGHS) She didn't kill him.

170
00:08:11.124 --> 00:08:14.003
If she wanted him dead. she wouldn't
have cooked him healthy meals once a week.

171
00:08:14.027 --> 00:08:16.238
Great. Let's just tell the police
and get Uncle Burton out of here

172
00:08:16.262 --> 00:08:18.595
before they ask
us anything else.

173
00:08:19.699 --> 00:08:21.565
GUS: Uncle Burton?

174
00:08:30.410 --> 00:08:33.209
All right. check it out.

175
00:08:33.813 --> 00:08:36.442
I went to Candy Emporium.
This time for research.

176
00:08:36.516 --> 00:08:39.782
There are over 100 flavors
of lollipop on the market.

177
00:08:39.853 --> 00:08:42.618
not one of which turns your
tongue black. Can you believe that?

178
00:08:42.689 --> 00:08:43.918
What are you talking about?

179
00:08:44.024 --> 00:08:46.858
Right before we left. I caught a
quick glimpse of the critic's mouth.

180
00:08:46.926 --> 00:08:48.792
His tongue was coated black.

181
00:08:48.862 --> 00:08:52.128
Now what else could possibly
cause something like that?

182
00:08:52.198 --> 00:08:53.996
Bismuth subsalicylate.

183
00:08:54.067 --> 00:08:55.544
That dude that used to
play for the Mavericks?

184
00:08:55.568 --> 00:08:56.627
No. Shawn.

185
00:08:56.703 --> 00:08:59.332
It's the active ingredient in
those pink stomach medications.

186
00:08:59.406 --> 00:09:02.740
He must've had some. Look. let's
talk about this later. My uncle is...

187
00:09:02.809 --> 00:09:03.833
Gus. What?

188
00:09:03.910 --> 00:09:06.038
The critic was murdered.

189
00:09:06.112 --> 00:09:07.590
I thought you said
the wife didn't kill him.

190
00:09:07.614 --> 00:09:08.809
She didn't.

191
00:09:08.882 --> 00:09:11.147
He was complaining of an
upset stomach before dinner.

192
00:09:11.217 --> 00:09:14.449
He asked for chicken soup. That's
the ultimate "I'm feeling sick" meal.

193
00:09:14.521 --> 00:09:17.855
Except. of course. for a tub of bacon
grease and hot dog water. But usually...

194
00:09:17.924 --> 00:09:22.385
Shawn. this place is a sty. Maybe you
ought to tidy up once in a while. huh?

195
00:09:22.462 --> 00:09:24.328
Or did you forget that
you're the assistant?

196
00:09:24.397 --> 00:09:27.731
You are absolutely right. sir.

197
00:09:28.134 --> 00:09:31.798
The person who's not the psychic detective
should be in charge of all the cleaning.

198
00:09:31.871 --> 00:09:32.964
It just makes sense.

199
00:09:33.039 --> 00:09:37.067
Meanwhile. Gus here has new psychic
knowledge about yesterday's case.

200
00:09:37.143 --> 00:09:39.203
Yeah? No. I don't. Shawn.

201
00:09:39.279 --> 00:09:42.943
I mean. I shouldn't spend so much
time working when I've got family in town.

202
00:09:43.016 --> 00:09:44.541
Oh. don't be ridiculous. Burton.

203
00:09:44.617 --> 00:09:48.054
You think <i>Diagnosis Murder</i> ever
let family get in the way of his work?

204
00:09:48.121 --> 00:09:52.058
Another excellent point. I bet
<i>Diagnosis Murder</i> never did that.

205
00:09:52.125 --> 00:09:56.756
Go ahead. Gus. Call upon the spirits.
Ask them what happened to the dead critic.

206
00:09:56.963 --> 00:09:58.625
Fine.

207
00:10:00.500 --> 00:10:02.935
(SNIFFING)

208
00:10:05.505 --> 00:10:09.237
(CROONING) Oh. spirits.

209
00:10:09.309 --> 00:10:13.974
Always willing to
lend a helping hand.

210
00:10:14.080 --> 00:10:16.640
This psychic stuff can
get a little wimpy. huh?

211
00:10:16.716 --> 00:10:19.413
At least he's not doing
it in a tutu and Capezios.

212
00:10:19.486 --> 00:10:24.891
I ask you to help me solve
the murder of Vince Wagner.

213
00:10:25.158 --> 00:10:28.686
Show me what transpired.

214
00:10:31.564 --> 00:10:33.465
I'm seeing something.

215
00:10:36.703 --> 00:10:40.071
I'm seeing... I'm seeing...

216
00:10:41.875 --> 00:10:44.071
I don't know what I'm seeing.

217
00:10:44.144 --> 00:10:47.546
Wait. wait. It's
coming clearer now.

218
00:10:48.515 --> 00:10:54.512
Somebody put something
in his food at a restaurant.

219
00:10:56.156 --> 00:10:59.354
And that is what made him sick.

220
00:11:00.460 --> 00:11:04.727
Sick to the point
of having a seizure.

221
00:11:04.797 --> 00:11:06.356
No. no. no. No?

222
00:11:09.202 --> 00:11:14.368
That's what killed...
That's what killed his nose.

223
00:11:14.440 --> 00:11:16.136
What?

224
00:11:17.277 --> 00:11:19.007
That's what killed him.

225
00:11:19.078 --> 00:11:23.174
Ooh! Gus. you are so
amazing with that stuff.

226
00:11:23.249 --> 00:11:25.377
(CHUCKLING) If it wasn't
for his psychic talents.

227
00:11:25.451 --> 00:11:29.013
I'd have to get some lame job at a
pharmaceutical company or something.

228
00:11:29.088 --> 00:11:31.250
That happens to be a very
exciting industry. Shawn.

229
00:11:31.324 --> 00:11:34.136
Now. let's go and tell the police our
new revelation. Uncle Burton. wait here.

230
00:11:34.160 --> 00:11:36.629
No way. If I wanted to
sit alone in a dirty room.

231
00:11:36.696 --> 00:11:38.164
I'd have stayed at
home with my wife.

232
00:11:38.231 --> 00:11:40.996
(CHUCKLES) I'm
going with you guys.

233
00:11:43.770 --> 00:11:45.170
Killed his nose? You didn't...

234
00:11:45.238 --> 00:11:48.118
What's wrong with you? How do you
kill a nose? You said like this. Shawn.

235
00:11:52.545 --> 00:11:54.985
Shawn. that visitor's badge is
not gonna hold him up for long.

236
00:11:55.048 --> 00:11:56.559
I can't be psychic
in front of the cops.

237
00:11:56.583 --> 00:11:58.108
Don't worry. I have a plan.

238
00:11:58.184 --> 00:12:00.415
I'm gonna go in Vick's office.
You wait here. For what?

239
00:12:00.486 --> 00:12:03.752
My signal. The stuff you were
doing in the office? Genius. all of it.

240
00:12:03.823 --> 00:12:05.553
But I wanted you
to say "poison." Gus.

241
00:12:05.625 --> 00:12:07.253
Poison. Get it right this time.

242
00:12:07.327 --> 00:12:08.537
This time? Shawn.
what are you about to...

243
00:12:08.561 --> 00:12:10.530
There's no time to explain.

244
00:12:10.597 --> 00:12:12.293
Ham pencils!

245
00:12:12.465 --> 00:12:17.768
Sheila E. tomato bark.
Velvety shark toast. Shark toast!

246
00:12:18.071 --> 00:12:20.472
Is there something wrong
with you. Mr. Spencer?

247
00:12:20.540 --> 00:12:22.600
You picked today to
ask him that question?

248
00:12:22.675 --> 00:12:24.871
Dude. Lassy. what
happened to your arm?

249
00:12:24.944 --> 00:12:25.988
I don't want to talk about it.

250
00:12:26.012 --> 00:12:27.056
Yeah. He won't tell us. either.

251
00:12:27.080 --> 00:12:29.692
And what were you saying when you
came in? I couldn't understand any of it.

252
00:12:29.716 --> 00:12:32.556
Oh. Jules. it's this case. These
visions I'm having. they're so intense.

253
00:12:32.585 --> 00:12:37.114
I can't even describe them. Every time I
open my mouth. the wrong fishes come out.

254
00:12:37.190 --> 00:12:39.318
You mean words?
Isn't that what I said?

255
00:12:39.392 --> 00:12:42.692
Oh. no. If only there was someone
here that could translate. You know?

256
00:12:42.762 --> 00:12:44.840
Someone who's known me so
long they understand everything I say.

257
00:12:44.864 --> 00:12:48.096
Someone just slightly
less handsome than I am.

258
00:12:49.469 --> 00:12:50.493
Gus!

259
00:12:50.570 --> 00:12:52.801
Perfect. This is perfect.
Gus! Gus. get in here!

260
00:12:52.872 --> 00:12:53.771
GUS: What?

261
00:12:53.840 --> 00:12:57.470
Oh! Mambo beef puddles!
Swirly. whirly jungle pants!

262
00:12:57.543 --> 00:13:01.105
(PANTING) Quick. translate
that in normal words for us.

263
00:13:01.180 --> 00:13:03.911
Man. they made me fill this thing
out for six pages of paperwork

264
00:13:03.983 --> 00:13:06.161
and didn't even put my picture
on it. Sorry. who are you?

265
00:13:06.185 --> 00:13:08.450
No one ask anymore
questions. No one.

266
00:13:08.921 --> 00:13:12.085
Concentrate. Gus. Tell
us what all this means.

267
00:13:12.925 --> 00:13:16.828
Swirly. whirly jungle pants.

268
00:13:16.963 --> 00:13:21.401
It means the critic ate
something he wasn't supposed to.

269
00:13:21.467 --> 00:13:22.799
Two bones and a skull.

270
00:13:22.869 --> 00:13:24.394
Two bones and a skull. Poison!

271
00:13:24.470 --> 00:13:27.372
Yes. The critic was poisoned.

272
00:13:27.440 --> 00:13:29.841
Man. this is better
than <i>Ghost Whisperer.</i>

273
00:13:29.909 --> 00:13:32.845
Guys. we checked the
wife's soup. It's clean.

274
00:13:32.945 --> 00:13:34.723
And wait. I am now supposed
to believe that Guster here...

275
00:13:34.747 --> 00:13:36.773
Carnival stunt
muffin. Huh? What?

276
00:13:36.849 --> 00:13:38.283
It wasn't the wife.

277
00:13:38.351 --> 00:13:41.150
The critic was
poisoned at a restaurant.

278
00:13:42.121 --> 00:13:45.922
Now that makes sense. Wagner was
pretty harsh on his own wife's cooking.

279
00:13:45.992 --> 00:13:48.359
He was probably even harder
on the restaurants he reviewed.

280
00:13:48.428 --> 00:13:51.193
He could've easily been poisoned
by a chef who got a bad review.

281
00:13:51.297 --> 00:13:52.321
Mmm-hmm.

282
00:13:52.398 --> 00:13:54.663
You think so? ALL: Yes!

283
00:13:54.734 --> 00:13:56.794
Okay.

284
00:13:56.869 --> 00:14:00.362
Call the lab. I want a tox
report on my desk ASAP.

285
00:14:00.440 --> 00:14:01.550
You're actually
listening to this?

286
00:14:01.574 --> 00:14:04.703
Well. we've gotten information
in stranger ways before.

287
00:14:04.777 --> 00:14:06.245
It never hurts to check it out.

288
00:14:06.512 --> 00:14:08.572
Burton. that was fantastic.

289
00:14:08.748 --> 00:14:10.216
How do you do that stuff?

290
00:14:10.283 --> 00:14:12.411
He can't talk right
now. Uncle Burton.

291
00:14:12.485 --> 00:14:15.284
Psychic episodes like that
leave him very. very parched.

292
00:14:15.355 --> 00:14:17.566
You see... No. no. no. no.
no. Let me get you some water.

293
00:14:17.590 --> 00:14:18.934
Down those stairs.
around the corner.

294
00:14:18.958 --> 00:14:20.620
Thank you.

295
00:14:20.693 --> 00:14:23.561
What do we do now? We're
gonna figure out what that critic ate.

296
00:14:23.629 --> 00:14:26.041
If he was poisoned by a chef. it had
to have been something he consumed

297
00:14:26.065 --> 00:14:27.727
in the 24 hours
leading up to his death.

298
00:14:27.800 --> 00:14:28.927
How do we do that?

299
00:14:29.001 --> 00:14:31.380
Well. Wagner's wife said he
brought all of his leftovers home. right?

300
00:14:31.404 --> 00:14:34.431
The refrigerator was packed
with takeout containers.

301
00:14:34.507 --> 00:14:39.502
The one on top was probably the most recent.
and the restaurant it came from was...

302
00:14:45.284 --> 00:14:47.446
The curvy A. The Curvy A?

303
00:14:47.520 --> 00:14:49.365
That doesn't sound like a
place that serves food. Shawn.

304
00:14:49.389 --> 00:14:51.467
It's not the name. It's the
symbol on top of the box.

305
00:14:51.491 --> 00:14:54.893
Come on. man. You eat out all the time.
What place has a big. swoopy. curving A?

306
00:14:54.961 --> 00:14:56.793
I don't know. What
does it look like?

307
00:14:56.896 --> 00:14:57.896
(SIGHS)

308
00:15:04.103 --> 00:15:05.298
Antonio's.

309
00:15:05.371 --> 00:15:06.532
Sweet.

310
00:15:06.606 --> 00:15:07.938
Why did you write on my hand?

311
00:15:08.007 --> 00:15:10.285
Why would I write on my own
hand? This thing is totally permanent.

312
00:15:10.309 --> 00:15:11.709
What? Shawn!

313
00:15:14.647 --> 00:15:16.558
Let's make this quick before
Uncle Burton starts thinking

314
00:15:16.582 --> 00:15:17.760
we're sticking
him with the check.

315
00:15:17.784 --> 00:15:19.962
Fire up the entrees for the
eight-top. COOK: You got it. boss.

316
00:15:19.986 --> 00:15:22.387
Mario. where are
my starters? Hurry up.

317
00:15:22.455 --> 00:15:25.015
MARIO: Almost ready.
Hey. Chef Antonio.

318
00:15:25.091 --> 00:15:26.435
We'd like to ask you
a couple of questions.

319
00:15:26.459 --> 00:15:29.827
Sorry. guys. No customers
allowed in the kitchen. <i>Area fresca.</i>

320
00:15:29.896 --> 00:15:32.040
No. we're not customers. We're
from the Health Department.

321
00:15:32.064 --> 00:15:33.828
Here for a surprise inspection.

322
00:15:33.900 --> 00:15:34.993
Again?

323
00:15:35.067 --> 00:15:38.094
We just had the surprise
inspection a few days ago.

324
00:15:38.171 --> 00:15:41.039
Why. is there a problem? Yes.
You weren't surprised enough.

325
00:15:41.207 --> 00:15:42.675
Let's make this quick.

326
00:15:43.976 --> 00:15:48.676
Walls and the floor are
clean. Drainage is clear.

327
00:15:48.748 --> 00:15:52.549
Hand-washing station is stocked
with soap and clean towels.

328
00:15:53.085 --> 00:15:57.750
Dry-food storage over there.
Walk-in freezer over here.

329
00:16:02.395 --> 00:16:04.193
Looks good.

330
00:16:04.263 --> 00:16:06.391
Aren't you supposed to
check the temperature?

331
00:16:06.466 --> 00:16:09.265
Of course. Gus. go ahead.
check the temperature.

332
00:16:09.335 --> 00:16:10.735
Me? Why do I have to do it?

333
00:16:10.803 --> 00:16:13.068
Dude. I'm wearing short sleeves.

334
00:16:13.139 --> 00:16:14.266
Okay.

335
00:16:15.775 --> 00:16:18.187
So. did you hear what happened
to the food critic down at the <i>Mirror?</i>

336
00:16:18.211 --> 00:16:19.907
That's some nasty business. huh?

337
00:16:19.979 --> 00:16:23.939
Sure. I heard about
Wagner. I don't say I'm sad.

338
00:16:24.016 --> 00:16:25.616
Ten years I've been
working in this town.

339
00:16:25.651 --> 00:16:28.815
That man never gave
my food a good review.

340
00:16:28.888 --> 00:16:30.823
Sounds like you're
not very fond of the guy.

341
00:16:30.890 --> 00:16:36.329
Vince Wagner made my life
miserable with his asinine reviews.

342
00:16:36.395 --> 00:16:40.298
Honestly. I am glad
that that bastard is dead.

343
00:16:40.366 --> 00:16:43.461
Chef Antonio?

344
00:16:43.536 --> 00:16:47.234
You're under arrest for the
murder of Vince Wagner. Take him.

345
00:16:47.306 --> 00:16:52.006
Murder? Is this a joke. huh? Who
put you up to this? Get your hands off...

346
00:16:52.078 --> 00:16:53.944
Jules. what's going on here?

347
00:16:54.013 --> 00:16:55.879
Tox screen came back positive.

348
00:16:55.948 --> 00:16:58.577
Apparently. Wagner ate a poisonous
mushroom called the death cap.

349
00:16:58.651 --> 00:16:59.651
What are you saying?

350
00:16:59.719 --> 00:17:03.079
There were death caps in the mushroom risotto
Wagner ate here the day before he died.

351
00:17:03.122 --> 00:17:05.284
We found the
leftovers in his fridge.

352
00:17:05.358 --> 00:17:08.556
Looks like you were
right. Shawn. Or Gus.

353
00:17:08.761 --> 00:17:10.957
Or whoever.

354
00:17:12.198 --> 00:17:15.168
What a relief. We caught
the guy. we solved the case

355
00:17:15.234 --> 00:17:17.669
and best of all. I don't
have to be psychic anymore.

356
00:17:17.737 --> 00:17:19.171
(LAUGHING)

357
00:17:24.810 --> 00:17:25.869
Uh-oh.

358
00:17:25.945 --> 00:17:27.106
What?

359
00:17:27.747 --> 00:17:29.807
We got the wrong guy.

360
00:17:29.882 --> 00:17:30.941
Man.

361
00:17:39.091 --> 00:17:40.855
Guys. it's not that complicated.

362
00:17:40.927 --> 00:17:44.193
Whenever a critic eats at his restaurant.
Antonio prepares the meal himself.

363
00:17:44.263 --> 00:17:48.223
Not this time. The mushrooms in the
takeout container were cut into cubes.

364
00:17:48.301 --> 00:17:50.361
Antonio cuts his
mushrooms into strips.

365
00:17:50.436 --> 00:17:53.099
Lassy. I have a really
strong vibe he didn't do this.

366
00:17:53.172 --> 00:17:55.300
Look. we know
Antonio hated Wagner.

367
00:17:55.374 --> 00:17:57.206
Wagner died from
eating his risotto.

368
00:17:57.276 --> 00:18:00.872
We have the risotto. We even have
Wagner's notes proving he ate the risotto.

369
00:18:00.947 --> 00:18:02.279
It's a slam dunk.

370
00:18:03.883 --> 00:18:04.883
(SIGHS)

371
00:18:08.955 --> 00:18:12.153
That's Wagner's notebook. It
says the risotto was cold. So?

372
00:18:12.224 --> 00:18:13.224
So.

373
00:18:14.694 --> 00:18:17.528
Whoa! The sandpaper
was the banana patch!

374
00:18:18.097 --> 00:18:19.929
I think he means
the risotto was cold.

375
00:18:19.999 --> 00:18:21.009
Thank you. Gus. You're welcome.

376
00:18:21.033 --> 00:18:24.401
Why would food be served cold
at a five-star restaurant unless...

377
00:18:24.470 --> 00:18:27.531
Unless the poisoned food
was cooked somewhere else.

378
00:18:28.007 --> 00:18:31.500
(EXCLAIMING) You know
what I think? Case is closed.

379
00:18:33.512 --> 00:18:34.536
(SIGHS)

380
00:18:34.614 --> 00:18:37.914
Hey. guys. I wanna thank you
for an incredible day. Burton.

381
00:18:37.984 --> 00:18:40.078
You're a regular <i>Rockford Files.</i>

382
00:18:40.152 --> 00:18:42.144
(LAUGHING)

383
00:18:44.857 --> 00:18:46.735
Did my uncle just thank
me for an incredible day?

384
00:18:46.759 --> 00:18:49.194
More important question.
How much TV does he watch?

385
00:18:49.261 --> 00:18:52.925
I'm serious. Shawn. My cousin took
him to the Super Bowl on a helicopter.

386
00:18:52.999 --> 00:18:54.142
and he never even
thanked him for that.

387
00:18:54.166 --> 00:18:56.431
I'm serious. too.
He's like this crazy

388
00:18:56.502 --> 00:18:59.768
tank-shaped encyclopedia
of detective shows.

389
00:18:59.839 --> 00:19:01.933
I bet he even saw <i>Manimal.</i>

390
00:19:02.008 --> 00:19:03.374
You're right. About <i>Manimal?</i>

391
00:19:03.442 --> 00:19:05.934
Shawn. we have to solve this
case before he leaves. Why?

392
00:19:06.012 --> 00:19:09.278
Because. I think I finally figured
out how to get back on his good side.

393
00:19:09.348 --> 00:19:11.460
I've been seeking Uncle
Burton's approval all my life.

394
00:19:11.484 --> 00:19:14.818
He's mean to everybody. But ever since
he started tagging along on this case.

395
00:19:14.887 --> 00:19:16.685
he's been kind of nice
to me. You know why?

396
00:19:16.756 --> 00:19:19.453
You don't have the braids
anymore. He likes detective shows.

397
00:19:19.525 --> 00:19:21.460
If I can solve this
case before he leaves.

398
00:19:21.527 --> 00:19:23.587
he may finally get over
the whole Gus-Burton thing.

399
00:19:23.663 --> 00:19:26.690
But I'm gonna need your help. All
right. fine. Mr. Psychic Detective.

400
00:19:26.766 --> 00:19:31.227
Tell me. since Antonio clearly
didn't kill the critic. who did?

401
00:19:31.303 --> 00:19:32.669
I don't know.

402
00:19:33.039 --> 00:19:35.201
Maybe we should find out
if anyone else hated him.

403
00:19:35.274 --> 00:19:36.351
See who else may
have had a motive.

404
00:19:36.375 --> 00:19:38.207
Shh! What?

405
00:19:38.277 --> 00:19:41.406
You're gonna start a crime-fighting
revolution with talk like that.

406
00:19:43.683 --> 00:19:45.584
Shawn. you say stuff
like that all the time.

407
00:19:51.991 --> 00:19:54.358
Phil Pritikin.
Mr. Editor-in-Chief.

408
00:19:54.427 --> 00:19:58.660
Shawn Spencer. Longtime
reader. first-time caller.

409
00:19:58.731 --> 00:20:00.256
What's going on with
the Sunday spread?

410
00:20:00.332 --> 00:20:02.301
Layout's waiting for your
approval on the mockup.

411
00:20:02.368 --> 00:20:04.633
Mockup. Funny word.
Like I was saying...

412
00:20:04.704 --> 00:20:06.400
Where's Salazar's
alderman story?

413
00:20:06.472 --> 00:20:08.483
She's typing it up. Do you
want copy to read it first?

414
00:20:08.507 --> 00:20:11.341
No. just send it straight
here. Anything else?

415
00:20:11.477 --> 00:20:13.855
You know. Phil. now that you
mention it. I would very much like to...

416
00:20:13.879 --> 00:20:15.370
Does he work here?

417
00:20:15.448 --> 00:20:16.507
I don't believe so. sir.

418
00:20:16.582 --> 00:20:19.609
Son. I'm a busy man. If you don't
work for me. I don't have the time.

419
00:20:19.685 --> 00:20:21.711
I just have a question
about Vince Wagner.

420
00:20:21.787 --> 00:20:24.120
Cooper. these
guys got questions.

421
00:20:24.857 --> 00:20:27.725
Ooh! I also have an
idea for a crossover strip

422
00:20:27.793 --> 00:20:30.456
where Dilbert finally
meets Marmaduke.

423
00:20:30.663 --> 00:20:32.791
Did you guys need something?

424
00:20:33.933 --> 00:20:36.869
Hi. I'm Burton
Guster with the SBPD.

425
00:20:37.002 --> 00:20:39.164
We're investigating the
murder of Vince Wagner.

426
00:20:39.238 --> 00:20:41.400
I'm Cooper. I was
Mr. Wagner's assistant.

427
00:20:41.474 --> 00:20:43.909
Great. Maybe you
can help us out.

428
00:20:43.976 --> 00:20:46.707
Do you know of anyone who may
have had a grudge against your boss?

429
00:20:46.779 --> 00:20:48.247
Are you serious?

430
00:20:48.681 --> 00:20:51.515
We call them the
Angry Chef Letters.

431
00:20:51.584 --> 00:20:53.280
Every chef who
ever got a bad review

432
00:20:53.352 --> 00:20:55.514
would write a nasty letter
to Mr. Wagner about it.

433
00:20:55.588 --> 00:20:57.580
So you're saying
this is all hate mail?

434
00:20:57.656 --> 00:20:59.591
I don't know if I'd
call it all hate mail.

435
00:20:59.658 --> 00:21:05.495
It ranges from mild dislike
mail to extreme abhorrence mail.

436
00:21:05.564 --> 00:21:07.226
How about "I wish
you were dead" mail?

437
00:21:07.299 --> 00:21:09.996
Oh. we have those.
too. Back here.

438
00:21:11.670 --> 00:21:13.782
Any one of these chefs could've
cooked the poisoned risotto

439
00:21:13.806 --> 00:21:15.331
and snuck it into
Antonio's restaurant.

440
00:21:15.441 --> 00:21:16.441
You're right.

441
00:21:16.509 --> 00:21:19.206
We should talk to all these chefs
before they open for business.

442
00:21:19.278 --> 00:21:22.510
Call the restaurants and
make a reservation. For Justice.

443
00:21:22.581 --> 00:21:24.693
Is justice the time or the
number of people in our party?

444
00:21:24.717 --> 00:21:27.619
Just call them. And make it
for three. Uncle Burton's coming.

445
00:21:27.686 --> 00:21:28.984
All right.

446
00:21:31.557 --> 00:21:33.719
So what did you
think of Vince Wagner?

447
00:21:33.793 --> 00:21:35.386
Looky here.

448
00:21:35.461 --> 00:21:38.021
He was a jackass.

449
00:21:38.097 --> 00:21:41.659
You know what he called
my award-winning jambalaya?

450
00:21:41.734 --> 00:21:43.635
"Jamba-lousy."

451
00:21:43.702 --> 00:21:49.039
Now tell me this ain't the best damn
jambalaya you never had in your life.

452
00:21:54.547 --> 00:21:57.292
Do you know what he wrote in his
review of my famous miso yellowtail roll?

453
00:21:57.316 --> 00:21:59.342
Mmm. "Miso disappointed."

454
00:21:59.418 --> 00:22:01.046
(LAUGHING)

455
00:22:01.120 --> 00:22:02.952
Don't laugh. It's not funny.

456
00:22:03.022 --> 00:22:04.684
No. it's not.

457
00:22:04.757 --> 00:22:09.422
Put it this way. He once referred to my
white chocolate tiramisu as "ass cake."

458
00:22:09.495 --> 00:22:11.464
Oh! Now that just seems mean.

459
00:22:11.530 --> 00:22:15.433
I didn't kill him. I was
here that night. cooking.

460
00:22:15.935 --> 00:22:18.700
Had a bunch of big groups.
Never even left the kitchen.

461
00:22:18.771 --> 00:22:20.899
Mmm-hmm. Mmm. Yeah.

462
00:22:21.440 --> 00:22:24.000
I was either in the kitchen or
out here talking to customers.

463
00:22:24.076 --> 00:22:26.636
I own this place. I have
to watch over everything.

464
00:22:26.712 --> 00:22:29.375
Every bowl. every noodle.
every chopstick. every fish...

465
00:22:29.448 --> 00:22:32.247
I didn't kill him. I definitely
thought about it a couple times.

466
00:22:32.318 --> 00:22:34.844
I never figured out why
that guy was so angry.

467
00:22:34.920 --> 00:22:37.389
He ate out at fancy
restaurants all the time for free.

468
00:22:37.456 --> 00:22:39.391
and. still. all he
did was complain.

469
00:22:39.458 --> 00:22:43.452
Ask her a few more questions.
Maybe she'll give us some cookies.

470
00:22:45.898 --> 00:22:50.359
I'm confused. Why are you here?
Wagner never even reviewed my restaurant.

471
00:22:50.836 --> 00:22:53.101
Oh. make it right. There it is.

472
00:22:55.608 --> 00:22:59.511
That was. without question. the
tastiest dead end we've ever gone down.

473
00:22:59.578 --> 00:23:02.742
Well. at least it wasn't a
complete waste of our time.

474
00:23:02.815 --> 00:23:05.694
It seems to me like any of these chefs
were way too busy to murder the critic.

475
00:23:05.718 --> 00:23:10.213
Matlock never ate this good. I'm going
back to the car and unbutton my pants.

476
00:23:10.289 --> 00:23:11.689
(CHUCKLING)

477
00:23:12.825 --> 00:23:16.523
You know. I've been thinking
about what that dessert chef said.

478
00:23:16.595 --> 00:23:20.032
Wagner got to eat out at fancy restaurants
every day on the newspaper's dime.

479
00:23:20.099 --> 00:23:21.761
If I was him. I'd be happy.

480
00:23:21.834 --> 00:23:24.497
I mean. who wouldn't
want to have that job?

481
00:23:24.570 --> 00:23:26.163
That's a good point.

482
00:23:26.238 --> 00:23:28.400
That's a really good point.
Gus. I think you're right.

483
00:23:28.474 --> 00:23:31.535
We were wrong about the chefs.
Maybe this wasn't about revenge at all.

484
00:23:31.610 --> 00:23:34.122
Maybe this was about somebody
wanting the restaurant critic's job.

485
00:23:34.146 --> 00:23:36.115
Someone who works at
the newspaper. Exactly.

486
00:23:36.181 --> 00:23:37.559
We need to get down
there and talk to the editor.

487
00:23:37.583 --> 00:23:39.882
Wait. wait. Shawn. he's
not going to talk to us.

488
00:23:39.952 --> 00:23:41.696
He doesn't talk to anybody
who doesn't work for him.

489
00:23:41.720 --> 00:23:44.383
Oh. I don't think
that'll be a problem.

490
00:24:00.306 --> 00:24:02.605
Okay. I think I have
something here.

491
00:24:03.208 --> 00:24:05.074
You. sir. are left-handed.

492
00:24:05.144 --> 00:24:06.908
You have a new baby at home.

493
00:24:06.979 --> 00:24:10.177
You just covered a story
somewhere in the Midwest.

494
00:24:10.482 --> 00:24:15.944
And you. You just really.
really need to pee. Just go.

495
00:24:19.625 --> 00:24:24.325
All right. you convinced me. Congratulations.
you're our new astrological forecaster.

496
00:24:24.430 --> 00:24:27.457
Now get out of here. You've got a job
to do. You've got a deadline to meet.

497
00:24:34.306 --> 00:24:35.968
Hey. dude. Did you
read my horoscopes?

498
00:24:36.041 --> 00:24:37.805
Yes. They're terrible.

499
00:24:37.876 --> 00:24:39.777
Horoscopes are
supposed to be vague

500
00:24:39.845 --> 00:24:42.190
so that people can interpret
them to mean whatever they want.

501
00:24:42.214 --> 00:24:43.876
Yours are all way too specific.

502
00:24:43.949 --> 00:24:45.850
I wrote them with
specific people in mind.

503
00:24:45.918 --> 00:24:50.379
"Aries. Calcium is especially
important to you right now.

504
00:24:50.456 --> 00:24:53.585
"Mr. Salt-and-Pepper
Hair with a maroon car.

505
00:24:53.659 --> 00:24:56.151
"There may also be a
promotion in your future.

506
00:24:56.228 --> 00:24:59.596
"Try walking backwards
through doorways for good luck."

507
00:24:59.698 --> 00:25:01.496
Carlton. are you
expecting a promotion?

508
00:25:01.567 --> 00:25:05.868
No. Come on. O'Hara. Don't be so
naive. It's a horoscope. It's nonsense.

509
00:25:05.938 --> 00:25:08.908
KAREN: Detective
Lassiter. may I have a word?

510
00:25:08.974 --> 00:25:10.203
Of course.

511
00:25:15.681 --> 00:25:17.582
Let's see. What's mine?

512
00:25:17.950 --> 00:25:24.686
"Libra. Your one true love will be wearing
sneakers and an Apple Jacks T-shirt."

513
00:25:24.857 --> 00:25:26.587
That's kind of a weird detail.

514
00:25:26.658 --> 00:25:28.251
Phil. heya.

515
00:25:28.327 --> 00:25:32.788
Wondering if I could ask you a couple of
questions about this restaurant critic job.

516
00:25:32.865 --> 00:25:35.232
Great. You too? Sorry?

517
00:25:35.300 --> 00:25:38.134
Everybody from the
ombudsman to the delivery boy

518
00:25:38.203 --> 00:25:40.297
wants to be the
new restaurant critic.

519
00:25:40.372 --> 00:25:42.534
I know it's the cushiest
gig in all of journalism.

520
00:25:42.608 --> 00:25:46.101
but I hired you to write horoscopes.
and that's what I expect you to do.

521
00:25:46.178 --> 00:25:48.738
Whoa. Phil. I think you're
getting the wrong idea.

522
00:25:48.814 --> 00:25:51.750
I just could sense that
you're totally swamped.

523
00:25:51.817 --> 00:25:55.413
Figured I'd come on in. offer
up my soothsayer services...

524
00:25:56.622 --> 00:25:57.646
Sayer services?

525
00:25:57.723 --> 00:26:01.057
Sooth services. Sooth services

526
00:26:01.126 --> 00:26:03.006
to help you pick the
best candidate for the job.

527
00:26:03.062 --> 00:26:07.898
I guess you are pretty sharp. Applications
are over there. Keep it quiet. though.

528
00:26:08.133 --> 00:26:09.761
Every single person
who works here

529
00:26:09.835 --> 00:26:12.498
is playing some sort of angle
to get the restaurant critic job.

530
00:26:12.571 --> 00:26:18.568
Sir? Meeting in five. You know.
these Cheetos are so crispy yet airy.

531
00:26:18.644 --> 00:26:23.139
and its subtle flavor is such a wonderful
contrast to its eye-catching color.

532
00:26:23.215 --> 00:26:24.945
I get it.

533
00:26:25.951 --> 00:26:28.250
Every day with the Cheetos.

534
00:26:28.320 --> 00:26:31.848
Shawn. there is 100
applications in here.

535
00:26:31.924 --> 00:26:34.758
That's 100 suspects. My
uncle's flight leaves today.

536
00:26:34.827 --> 00:26:37.667
We don't have time to talk to a
hundred people. Shawn. We don't need to.

537
00:26:37.729 --> 00:26:39.254
We just need to
talk to the one guy

538
00:26:39.331 --> 00:26:41.409
that can link one of those
people to the murder weapon.

539
00:26:41.433 --> 00:26:43.231
And who's that?

540
00:26:43.802 --> 00:26:46.795
<i>(SITAR PLAYING)</i>

541
00:26:49.675 --> 00:26:53.771
Mmm. Mmm. Delicious.

542
00:26:54.146 --> 00:26:56.081
Are you sure about this guy?

543
00:26:57.916 --> 00:27:00.476
He's the only mushroom
farmer in the tri-county area.

544
00:27:00.552 --> 00:27:02.783
If anyone can help us. he can.

545
00:27:03.956 --> 00:27:07.825
Mr. Mooney. thanks again for
taking the time to speak with us.

546
00:27:07.893 --> 00:27:09.623
(EXHALING)

547
00:27:10.028 --> 00:27:11.758
So. how many...

548
00:27:11.830 --> 00:27:13.594
How many types of
mushrooms do you grow here?

549
00:27:13.665 --> 00:27:15.510
Well. a couple of hundred.
depending on the season.

550
00:27:15.534 --> 00:27:19.027
Does that include a
mushroom called the death cap?

551
00:27:19.104 --> 00:27:21.015
Death cap? Heck. no. man.
Those things are poisonous.

552
00:27:21.039 --> 00:27:22.439
Besides. they only
grow in the wild.

553
00:27:22.508 --> 00:27:26.377
Well. let's say we were looking
for the death cap around here.

554
00:27:26.445 --> 00:27:27.879
Where would we find it?

555
00:27:27.946 --> 00:27:31.940
Well. I know a few places
in the hills. Why do you ask?

556
00:27:32.017 --> 00:27:33.610
Why do you ask why do I ask?

557
00:27:33.685 --> 00:27:35.051
(LAUGHING)

558
00:27:35.120 --> 00:27:37.248
Why do you ask why
do I ask why do you ask?

559
00:27:37.322 --> 00:27:40.451
Why do you ask why do I
ask why do you ask... Shawn.

560
00:27:40.526 --> 00:27:42.188
I'm just curious.

561
00:27:42.261 --> 00:27:46.096
Yeah. well. a guy came in here a couple of
weeks ago. and he had the exact same question.

562
00:27:46.165 --> 00:27:47.525
Do you remember
this person's name?

563
00:27:47.566 --> 00:27:51.435
Can't say that I do. But I remember
exactly what he looked like.

564
00:27:51.703 --> 00:27:53.035
Can you give us a description?

565
00:27:53.105 --> 00:27:56.974
Yeah. okay. The guy was
about nine feet tall. right?

566
00:27:57.042 --> 00:28:01.275
He had sunshine coming out of his mouth.
and he had a hippopotamus for a hand.

567
00:28:01.346 --> 00:28:02.490
I don't think I have
any more questions.

568
00:28:02.514 --> 00:28:04.244
Yup. That'll do it.

569
00:28:05.150 --> 00:28:07.362
Okay. Uncle Burton. Just let me
know when you're all packed up

570
00:28:07.386 --> 00:28:09.981
and I'll pick you up and take
you to the airport. All right.

571
00:28:10.055 --> 00:28:12.183
We spent two hours riding
up to that mushroom farm.

572
00:28:12.257 --> 00:28:13.535
and we're right back
to where we started.

573
00:28:13.559 --> 00:28:15.118
Oh.

574
00:28:15.194 --> 00:28:17.629
Don't be such a gloomy you.
Gus. Look at the bright side.

575
00:28:17.696 --> 00:28:18.994
Now we know the killer is a he.

576
00:28:19.064 --> 00:28:22.159
And that he has a hippopotamus
for a hand. That helps us out a lot.

577
00:28:22.234 --> 00:28:24.226
Whoa! Dad. What
are you doing here?

578
00:28:24.303 --> 00:28:25.896
"Sagittarius.

579
00:28:25.971 --> 00:28:29.669
"Please return the BB gun you confiscated
from your son in the second grade.

580
00:28:29.741 --> 00:28:31.767
"P.S. You are a crankypants."

581
00:28:31.843 --> 00:28:32.987
That's an amazing coincidence.

582
00:28:33.011 --> 00:28:35.290
Didn't you confiscate a BB gun
from me in the second grade?

583
00:28:35.314 --> 00:28:37.874
All right. look. Shawn.
Here's your stuff.

584
00:28:37.950 --> 00:28:40.943
Next time you want something
from me. be an adult and ask for it.

585
00:28:41.019 --> 00:28:43.545
Passing yourself off as a
psychic. that's bad enough.

586
00:28:43.622 --> 00:28:45.523
But horoscopes? Shawn... Shawn!

587
00:28:45.591 --> 00:28:49.494
What if some idiot out there reads
this crap and decides to take it seriously?

588
00:28:49.561 --> 00:28:50.790
Dad. it clearly states that

589
00:28:50.862 --> 00:28:54.424
"Astrological forecasts are for
entertainment purposes only."

590
00:28:54.566 --> 00:28:56.228
Besides. I only took
the job for a case.

591
00:28:56.301 --> 00:28:58.497
We're investigating the
restaurant critic murder.

592
00:28:58.570 --> 00:28:59.814
The cops already have a suspect.

593
00:28:59.838 --> 00:29:02.000
but we're pretty sure that
Chef Antonio was framed.

594
00:29:02.074 --> 00:29:06.535
Oh. then I assume you know all
about the veggie burger incident. then.

595
00:29:06.612 --> 00:29:07.705
(SCOFFING)

596
00:29:07.779 --> 00:29:09.857
Of course we know about
the veggie burger incident. Dad.

597
00:29:09.881 --> 00:29:12.612
We're professional
detectives. Gus?

598
00:29:12.684 --> 00:29:14.152
Googling it.

599
00:29:14.486 --> 00:29:17.999
Sean. you know. maybe instead of wasting your
time writing this garbage for the newspaper

600
00:29:18.023 --> 00:29:20.549
you might try reading
it once in a while.

601
00:29:20.626 --> 00:29:23.460
A couple of months ago. vegetarian
customers at Antonio's restaurant

602
00:29:23.528 --> 00:29:26.396
started complaining about how
bland the vegetarian burgers were.

603
00:29:26.465 --> 00:29:29.765
Now. in my personal opinion. if
you eat a burger without beef in it...

604
00:29:29.835 --> 00:29:32.236
BOTH: You've lost the
right to complain about flavor.

605
00:29:32.304 --> 00:29:35.183
I've heard that speech before. Just call
someone a hippie and get to the point.

606
00:29:35.207 --> 00:29:38.075
The point is. Antonio decided
to make the burgers tastier

607
00:29:38.143 --> 00:29:40.135
by adding beef
broth to the recipe.

608
00:29:40.212 --> 00:29:43.910
Oh. great. All the complaints
stopped. Until some crazy vegan lady...

609
00:29:43.982 --> 00:29:45.917
By the name of Dwyer?
Found out about it

610
00:29:46.418 --> 00:29:49.946
and started organizing boycotts
against Antonio's restaurant.

611
00:29:50.022 --> 00:29:51.266
They've been feuding ever since.

612
00:29:51.290 --> 00:29:55.057
This guy secretly fed beef to vegetarians?
Why are we trying to get him out of jail?

613
00:29:55.127 --> 00:29:58.529
Because he didn't kill the critic.
Take a look at this article. Shawn.

614
00:29:58.597 --> 00:30:01.089
She advocates any action to
put Chef Antonio out of business

615
00:30:01.166 --> 00:30:02.828
for the veggie burger incident.

616
00:30:02.901 --> 00:30:04.870
She calls herself
the Vegan Vigilante.

617
00:30:04.936 --> 00:30:07.030
(SCOFFS) How
very villainous of her.

618
00:30:07.105 --> 00:30:09.904
You think she could've framed
Antonio for Wagner's death or what?

619
00:30:09.975 --> 00:30:13.139
Only one way to find out. Do you
know where this Dwyer lady might be?

620
00:30:13.211 --> 00:30:16.648
Sure. I saw her at the drive
through a couple of days ago.

621
00:30:16.715 --> 00:30:19.913
Well. that's very helpful. Dad. What
makes you think she'll be there today?

622
00:30:19.985 --> 00:30:23.012
(CROWD CHANTING IN
UNISON) Meat is murder!

623
00:30:23.088 --> 00:30:24.989
Stop eating your
fellow creatures!

624
00:30:25.057 --> 00:30:27.686
All animals have
got the right to live!

625
00:30:28.226 --> 00:30:31.196
Meat is murder! I hate
it when my dad's right.

626
00:30:31.263 --> 00:30:36.167
Stop eating your fellow creatures!
All animals have got the right to live!

627
00:30:36.234 --> 00:30:40.296
Yo! Vegan Vigilante lady.
How long you been out here?

628
00:30:40.372 --> 00:30:41.396
Three days.

629
00:30:41.473 --> 00:30:46.343
We heard that you had a grudge with Chef
Antonio. Were you near his restaurant recently?

630
00:30:46.411 --> 00:30:49.540
Yeah. I lead a protest outside
of his place on Tuesday night.

631
00:30:49.614 --> 00:30:51.708
(CROWD CONTINUES
CHANTING) Tuesday night?

632
00:30:52.250 --> 00:30:54.014
Excuse us.

633
00:30:54.753 --> 00:30:56.654
That was the same night
the critic was poisoned.

634
00:30:56.722 --> 00:30:59.624
Dude. I think we just
found our killer. Nice.

635
00:30:59.691 --> 00:31:03.992
Detective Lassiter. SBPD.
Who's in charge of this freak fest?

636
00:31:04.062 --> 00:31:05.928
Guys! We got your message.

637
00:31:05.997 --> 00:31:09.195
Will you please tell us what
this has to do with the case?

638
00:31:11.069 --> 00:31:12.230
Nice shirt.

639
00:31:12.304 --> 00:31:13.636
Thanks.

640
00:31:13.972 --> 00:31:15.600
Did you buy that
today. by any chance?

641
00:31:15.674 --> 00:31:17.302
(CHUCKLING) This old rag?

642
00:31:17.376 --> 00:31:20.437
No. I've had this thing
for just about forever.

643
00:31:20.579 --> 00:31:23.879
Remember when I sent off those
cereal box tops to get this thing?

644
00:31:23.949 --> 00:31:25.679
You didn't do that. Sure. I did.

645
00:31:25.751 --> 00:31:28.162
No. you didn't. It was the same year
you got your first Cabbage Patch...

646
00:31:28.186 --> 00:31:29.677
Shh! I remember.

647
00:31:29.755 --> 00:31:31.519
Why do you ask.
Jules? No reason.

648
00:31:31.590 --> 00:31:34.736
All right. this whack job is in violation
of at least six different municipal codes

649
00:31:34.760 --> 00:31:38.288
and she smells like curly fries. I
say we cut her loose. take her down.

650
00:31:38.363 --> 00:31:39.440
Where's the restaurant manager?

651
00:31:39.464 --> 00:31:41.558
He's probably inside
managing the restaurant.

652
00:31:41.633 --> 00:31:43.192
Copy that.

653
00:31:45.504 --> 00:31:49.566
Wait for it. Wait for it.

654
00:31:49.741 --> 00:31:50.936
Is there a problem?

655
00:31:51.009 --> 00:31:54.468
No. No. I'm just making
sure I'm not being followed.

656
00:31:55.447 --> 00:31:57.678
A good cop. always
aware of his surroundings.

657
00:31:58.049 --> 00:32:00.348
(CROWD CHANTING)

658
00:32:00.752 --> 00:32:02.482
(CRASHING)

659
00:32:03.155 --> 00:32:05.056
I had better go help him.

660
00:32:06.892 --> 00:32:08.417
Uncle Burton.

661
00:32:08.493 --> 00:32:11.292
Burton. I got here
as soon as I could.

662
00:32:11.363 --> 00:32:13.389
Who are all these
strange people?

663
00:32:13.465 --> 00:32:14.905
It's all a part of
our investigation.

664
00:32:14.966 --> 00:32:17.145
We had to come check out a lead.
Thanks for meeting me down here.

665
00:32:17.169 --> 00:32:18.228
Oh. no problem.

666
00:32:18.303 --> 00:32:20.581
That ride in the cab gave me
a chance to fill out this postcard

667
00:32:20.605 --> 00:32:23.803
letting everybody in the family
know about our psychic detective.

668
00:32:23.875 --> 00:32:25.036
(LAUGHING)

669
00:32:25.110 --> 00:32:27.636
Well. I hope you saved
some room on there.

670
00:32:27.712 --> 00:32:29.044
'cause I just solved the case.

671
00:32:29.114 --> 00:32:30.138
Yeah?

672
00:32:30.215 --> 00:32:35.711
A few months ago. Chef Antonio put beef broth
in his veggie burgers at his restaurant.

673
00:32:35.787 --> 00:32:39.121
infuriating vegetarians
all over Santa Barbara.

674
00:32:39.524 --> 00:32:44.155
That woman tried to put the chef
out of business. but it didn't work.

675
00:32:44.296 --> 00:32:49.064
So instead. she poisoned the
critic and framed chef Antonio for it.

676
00:32:49.134 --> 00:32:52.798
What are you talking about? I never
poisoned anybody. You guys are nuts.

677
00:32:52.871 --> 00:32:57.172
Hey. watch the way you talk to my nephew.
'cause he can see right into your soul.

678
00:32:57.242 --> 00:32:58.904
You were there on
the night it happened.

679
00:32:58.977 --> 00:33:02.641
And I'm sure that seeing the chef
behind bars must make you pretty happy.

680
00:33:02.714 --> 00:33:07.743
Well. of course it makes me happy. He didn't
have respect for the rights of animals.

681
00:33:07.953 --> 00:33:09.353
Meat is murder.

682
00:33:09.421 --> 00:33:12.289
But murder is also
murder. Miss Dwyer!

683
00:33:12.357 --> 00:33:15.657
We'll be right there. Guys. there's
been a development in your case.

684
00:33:15.727 --> 00:33:19.425
Someone died from eating death caps
that were discarded downtown yesterday.

685
00:33:19.498 --> 00:33:20.796
Yesterday? Yesterday?

686
00:33:20.866 --> 00:33:23.893
Dude. it couldn't be her. She's
been chained to a pole for three days.

687
00:33:23.969 --> 00:33:26.409
Plus. we're nowhere near
downtown. She still could've done it.

688
00:33:26.438 --> 00:33:27.849
She could've easily
have slipped out of here

689
00:33:27.873 --> 00:33:29.150
and done it when
no one was around.

690
00:33:29.174 --> 00:33:30.972
Actually. she couldn't have.

691
00:33:31.042 --> 00:33:34.137
We have a rough description of the
suspect who threw the mushrooms away.

692
00:33:34.212 --> 00:33:37.239
It was a six-foot-tall man.

693
00:33:42.220 --> 00:33:44.314
Psychic. Bogus.

694
00:33:48.226 --> 00:33:50.252
Our second victim
was a homeless man.

695
00:33:50.328 --> 00:33:53.856
Ate a bag of death caps he saw
being tossed in a dumpster yesterday.

696
00:33:53.932 --> 00:33:57.699
then went to the health clinic today
after complaining of abdominal pains.

697
00:33:57.769 --> 00:33:58.998
He died a few hours ago.

698
00:33:59.070 --> 00:34:01.115
What else do we know about
the person who discarded them?

699
00:34:01.139 --> 00:34:05.907
Not much. The victim died before he was
able to give us an accurate description.

700
00:34:05.977 --> 00:34:09.914
And Chef Antonio was in custody.
so it looks like he's innocent.

701
00:34:09.981 --> 00:34:11.381
Not if he had an accomplice.

702
00:34:11.449 --> 00:34:14.462
Now that we've got the chef. his partner's
out there trying to dispose of evidence.

703
00:34:14.486 --> 00:34:16.785
Let's go down to lock
up and talk to that chef.

704
00:34:17.155 --> 00:34:18.783
Thanks.

705
00:34:19.891 --> 00:34:21.689
See you later.

706
00:34:23.428 --> 00:34:24.691
Where was the dumpster located?

707
00:34:24.763 --> 00:34:26.527
At the corner of
Laguna and Vista.

708
00:34:28.533 --> 00:34:30.593
Shawn. we were
on the right track.

709
00:34:30.669 --> 00:34:32.934
Laguna and Vista is across
the street from the newspaper.

710
00:34:33.004 --> 00:34:35.082
Whoever threw out those
mushrooms works at the paper.

711
00:34:35.106 --> 00:34:36.699
We have to go back over there.

712
00:34:36.775 --> 00:34:38.319
Uncle Burton's flight
leaves in an hour.

713
00:34:38.343 --> 00:34:40.744
I don't care. Do you know
what's at stake here. Shawn?

714
00:34:40.812 --> 00:34:42.371
My entire future with my family.

715
00:34:42.447 --> 00:34:45.226
Yeah. That. two unsolved murders.
and an innocent man who's still in jail.

716
00:34:45.250 --> 00:34:46.741
But your family. too.

717
00:34:46.818 --> 00:34:48.563
Dude. we still have
no idea who the killer is.

718
00:34:48.587 --> 00:34:50.598
And it's gonna take longer
than an hour to figure that out.

719
00:34:50.622 --> 00:34:52.215
(KNOCK ON GLASS)

720
00:34:52.924 --> 00:34:55.587
Fine. Let's go to
the stupid airport.

721
00:34:57.729 --> 00:35:02.258
Listen. Burton. maybe you're not
all to blame for fouling up this case.

722
00:35:02.334 --> 00:35:06.203
I mean. I can't help but think that
you'd do better at this detective business

723
00:35:06.271 --> 00:35:08.502
if you didn't have Shawn
weighing you down.

724
00:35:08.573 --> 00:35:11.042
I mean. I don't see what
he's bringing to the operation.

725
00:35:11.109 --> 00:35:12.975
You're psychic. he's not.

726
00:35:13.044 --> 00:35:14.706
What do you need him around for?

727
00:35:14.779 --> 00:35:17.078
You know. Gus.
your uncle has a point.

728
00:35:17.148 --> 00:35:20.380
What I'm trying to say is. it was <i>Murder.
She Wrote.</i> not <i>Murder. They Wrote.</i>

729
00:35:20.452 --> 00:35:21.750
That's true.

730
00:35:21.920 --> 00:35:25.413
Oh. this is great. I left some
of my clothes at the hotel.

731
00:35:25.490 --> 00:35:28.050
Maybe if somebody hadn't
rushed me down to the burger stand.

732
00:35:28.126 --> 00:35:30.960
I wouldn't have forgotten to
pack my new yellow hippo shirt.

733
00:35:31.029 --> 00:35:32.258
You mean your hip shirts?

734
00:35:32.330 --> 00:35:36.062
No. I mean my hippo shirt. I bought a
couple of them down on State Street.

735
00:35:36.134 --> 00:35:38.603
You know. normally. I
don't go for modern fashion.

736
00:35:38.670 --> 00:35:42.232
but these hippo shirts. they
make my arms look so huge.

737
00:35:42.641 --> 00:35:46.305
They've got a nice little hippo
logo right on the sleeve. See?

738
00:35:46.378 --> 00:35:47.607
Nice.

739
00:35:49.648 --> 00:35:54.951
He had sunshine coming out of his
mouth. He had a hippopotamus for a hand.

740
00:35:56.788 --> 00:35:58.882
Gus. I just figured it out.

741
00:35:59.324 --> 00:36:02.226
Who had the best access to the
person picking the next restaurant critic?

742
00:36:02.293 --> 00:36:04.660
Think about it.

743
00:36:04.729 --> 00:36:07.392
Uncle Burton. you might
be a little late for your flight.

744
00:36:12.570 --> 00:36:16.837
So I'm proud to announce that
our new restaurant critic will be

745
00:36:16.908 --> 00:36:18.240
my hard-working assistant. Nick!

746
00:36:18.309 --> 00:36:19.607
(EXCLAIMING)

747
00:36:19.678 --> 00:36:20.907
(APPLAUDING)

748
00:36:20.979 --> 00:36:24.040
Thank you so much.
sir. I'm so surprised.

749
00:36:24.115 --> 00:36:26.346
I honestly didn't expect
to get to this job at all.

750
00:36:26.418 --> 00:36:28.319
That's not exactly true. is it?

751
00:36:28.386 --> 00:36:29.877
Whoa. Gus.
Don't worry. I got it.

752
00:36:29.954 --> 00:36:32.514
GUS: You knew that Phil
Pritikin would give you this job.

753
00:36:32.590 --> 00:36:35.424
That's why you
murdered Vince Wagner.

754
00:36:35.493 --> 00:36:37.121
But Gus. we... I said I got it.

755
00:36:37.195 --> 00:36:39.426
Hang on. Hang on. You're
saying he's the killer?

756
00:36:39.497 --> 00:36:44.526
Yes. And I'm going to tell you
exactly how he did it. In just a second.

757
00:36:45.870 --> 00:36:47.168
You never told me how he did it.

758
00:36:47.238 --> 00:36:49.183
Why do you think I'm trying to
stop you? What are we gonna do?

759
00:36:49.207 --> 00:36:51.686
My uncle thinks I'm the psychic.
the newspaper thinks you're a psychic.

760
00:36:51.710 --> 00:36:53.975
and the cops think I'm
just translating your visions.

761
00:36:54.045 --> 00:36:55.707
Give me a second
to think. Hurry up.

762
00:36:55.780 --> 00:36:58.409
Okay. I have a plan. Blurt out
something nonsensical. Do it now.

763
00:36:58.483 --> 00:36:59.974
Keylaces! Shoeboards!
Pineapples!

764
00:37:00.051 --> 00:37:03.283
Oh. no. The visions have become
too complex for one person to decipher.

765
00:37:03.354 --> 00:37:04.652
Gus. might I offer my help?

766
00:37:04.723 --> 00:37:05.952
Yes. Shawn. you may.

767
00:37:06.024 --> 00:37:08.118
Magic head.

768
00:37:08.193 --> 00:37:10.025
Two heads working
together as one.

769
00:37:10.095 --> 00:37:14.362
(EXCLAIMING) You! You wanted the
most coveted job the paper had to offer.

770
00:37:14.432 --> 00:37:16.877
and you were in the good graces of
the one guy that could give it to you.

771
00:37:16.901 --> 00:37:20.201
But there was a problem.
Now. what was that problem?

772
00:37:21.206 --> 00:37:25.644
The problem was. Wagner was never
going to retire. So what did you do?

773
00:37:26.511 --> 00:37:29.345
You hatched a plan to
force Wagner off the job.

774
00:37:29.414 --> 00:37:33.875
The first thing you needed was a fall guy.
Unfortunately. Lee Majors wasn't available.

775
00:37:33.952 --> 00:37:35.921
(WHISPERING)

776
00:37:36.721 --> 00:37:39.987
Apparently. he was
available. He lives here in town.

777
00:37:40.058 --> 00:37:41.569
But he was a little
out of your price range.

778
00:37:41.593 --> 00:37:43.003
So you flipped through
Wagner's hate mail.

779
00:37:43.027 --> 00:37:46.657
and you discovered that Chef
Antonio was the perfect candidate.

780
00:37:46.731 --> 00:37:48.461
(EXCLAIMING)

781
00:37:49.234 --> 00:37:52.796
You knew Antonio's signature
dish was his wild mushroom risotto.

782
00:37:52.871 --> 00:37:55.238
So what did you do?

783
00:37:55.306 --> 00:37:58.765
(EXCLAIMING) You tracked
down some death cap mushrooms.

784
00:37:58.843 --> 00:38:01.176
and baked them into a risotto
that resembled Antonio's.

785
00:38:01.246 --> 00:38:02.286
But you made two mistakes.

786
00:38:02.347 --> 00:38:05.943
First. you sliced your mushrooms
into cubes instead of strips.

787
00:38:06.017 --> 00:38:07.017
And second.

788
00:38:07.051 --> 00:38:10.818
Wagner noticed that
his risotto was cold.

789
00:38:10.889 --> 00:38:14.257
Why would risotto be served
cold in a five-star restaurant?

790
00:38:14.325 --> 00:38:19.662
Because! Antonio didn't
cook it. You snuck it in.

791
00:38:19.731 --> 00:38:22.530
We just had the surprise
inspection a few days ago.

792
00:38:22.934 --> 00:38:26.302
A simple call to the county will confirm
that there were no real health inspectors

793
00:38:26.371 --> 00:38:28.465
at Antonio's
restaurant that night.

794
00:38:28.540 --> 00:38:30.975
You posed as one. and that
gave you the cover you needed

795
00:38:31.042 --> 00:38:34.444
<i>to switch out the risotto
with your poisoned batch.</i>

796
00:38:40.585 --> 00:38:43.646
(SCREAMING) Stop!

797
00:38:43.721 --> 00:38:47.988
Wagner died. Antonio was arrested. and
no one suspected you were the real killer.

798
00:38:48.059 --> 00:38:50.722
This is preposterous.
You can't just walk in here

799
00:38:50.795 --> 00:38:52.354
and accuse someone
of being a murderer.

800
00:38:52.463 --> 00:38:55.262
Well. actually. we can.

801
00:38:57.402 --> 00:38:59.268
Damn right. we can.

802
00:38:59.337 --> 00:39:02.865
The guy you went to about the mushrooms
remembers exactly what you look like.

803
00:39:02.941 --> 00:39:05.968
After you tone down the
drug-induced exaggerations. Yeah.

804
00:39:06.044 --> 00:39:10.072
Tall guy! Orange cheese
powder around the mouth.

805
00:39:10.148 --> 00:39:11.810
and a hippo logo on his sleeve.

806
00:39:11.883 --> 00:39:15.251
Al Mooney is insane. Nobody
will believe what he says.

807
00:39:15.320 --> 00:39:19.280
Hang on a minute. I don't believe
anyone said the witness's name.

808
00:39:19.424 --> 00:39:20.858
You're under arrest.

809
00:39:22.093 --> 00:39:23.254
Cuff him. guys.

810
00:39:23.328 --> 00:39:24.728
Busted.

811
00:39:24.796 --> 00:39:26.458
Hands behind your back. please.

812
00:39:26.531 --> 00:39:29.831
I wanna talk to a lawyer.
Yeah. sure. come on. Let's go.

813
00:39:31.336 --> 00:39:34.864
Looks like you're finally able to
communicate your visions again.

814
00:39:34.939 --> 00:39:36.771
It feels good to be back. Jules.

815
00:39:36.841 --> 00:39:38.819
As a matter of fact. I'm
having another vision right now.

816
00:39:38.843 --> 00:39:42.336
You and me celebrating
over dinner. drinks.

817
00:39:42.413 --> 00:39:45.247
Hmm. Sounds like
you're still a little off.

818
00:39:46.384 --> 00:39:47.384
Whoo!

819
00:39:47.452 --> 00:39:49.045
Another case solved. Yeah.

820
00:39:49.120 --> 00:39:50.600
Now let's just get
you to the airport.

821
00:39:50.655 --> 00:39:53.181
For what? My flight
left five minutes ago.

822
00:39:53.258 --> 00:39:55.989
Uh-oh. Are you mad?

823
00:39:56.060 --> 00:39:57.153
No.

824
00:39:57.228 --> 00:40:00.892
Why would I be mad
at you. Gus? Huh?

825
00:40:02.533 --> 00:40:05.970
Guys. there's been a bank robbery
downtown. Chief Vick's asking for you.

826
00:40:06.037 --> 00:40:10.441
Bank robbery? Man. that sounds exciting.
You guys don't mind if I tag along. do you?

827
00:40:10.508 --> 00:40:13.603
BOTH: Well... Well. of
course not. Wait for me.

828
00:40:14.812 --> 00:40:18.214
Don't worry. I have a plan.

829
00:40:22.253 --> 00:40:23.812
Gus. take it easy.

830
00:40:23.888 --> 00:40:26.881
And Shawn. don't forget to
vacuum the office every night.

831
00:40:26.958 --> 00:40:28.551
I'm all over it. Uncle Burton.

832
00:40:28.626 --> 00:40:32.893
As a matter of fact. you might just want to
check out this little ditty before you go.

833
00:40:32.964 --> 00:40:34.057
What's that?

834
00:40:34.132 --> 00:40:37.227
Well. Gus. I learned from your uncle
that I need to be a better assistant.

835
00:40:37.302 --> 00:40:40.295
So I've taken the liberty to draw
up a new employment contract

836
00:40:40.371 --> 00:40:44.467
that spells out the duties of the
psychic detective's non-psychic associate.

837
00:40:44.542 --> 00:40:45.771
Assistant.

838
00:40:45.843 --> 00:40:47.277
Assistant.

839
00:40:47.345 --> 00:40:50.543
Things like cleaning. emptying
the trash. doing the dishes. and...

840
00:40:50.615 --> 00:40:52.311
Thank you. Shawn.
I'll sign it later.

841
00:40:52.383 --> 00:40:54.875
No. sign it now before
he changes his mind.

842
00:40:54.953 --> 00:40:56.512
Yeah. Gus. Before
I change my mind.

843
00:40:56.587 --> 00:40:58.749
I'm not signing that.
Shawn. And why the hell not?

844
00:40:58.823 --> 00:41:00.018
'Cause.

845
00:41:02.560 --> 00:41:04.552
Look. Uncle Burton.

846
00:41:04.629 --> 00:41:07.326
I gotta tell you something and I
know you're gonna be disappointed.

847
00:41:07.398 --> 00:41:09.230
I know. I know. You're confused.

848
00:41:09.334 --> 00:41:13.430
Because I'm here. you don't know
whether to sign it "Burton" or "Gus."

849
00:41:13.504 --> 00:41:16.440
Let me tell you something. Your
psychic abilities help solve crimes.

850
00:41:16.507 --> 00:41:21.639
It makes the world a better place. Thanks
to you. the Burton legacy will live on.

851
00:41:22.380 --> 00:41:24.406
So sign that thing
any way you want to.

852
00:41:24.482 --> 00:41:26.246
You got my blessing.

853
00:41:28.019 --> 00:41:30.511
Is that what you
were gonna tell me?

854
00:41:30.788 --> 00:41:32.313
Pretty much. Yeah.

855
00:41:32.390 --> 00:41:35.690
Okay. Take it easy. fellas.

856
00:41:36.728 --> 00:41:37.728
We'll see ya.

857
00:41:45.803 --> 00:41:48.830
Well. there you have it. You
can sign it any way you want.

858
00:41:48.906 --> 00:41:51.034
I'm not signing that. Shawn.

859
00:41:51.109 --> 00:41:52.873
Dude. you can sign
anything you want.

860
00:41:52.944 --> 00:41:54.173
He said.

861
00:41:55.079 --> 00:41:56.741
You could sign it Don Cheadle.

862
00:41:56.814 --> 00:41:57.941
GUS: I'm not signing it!

863
00:41:58.016 --> 00:42:01.009
SHAWN: Debrick Shaw
Stillington? Delmar Lindo?

864
00:42:09.427 --> 00:42:13.023
<i>In between the lines
there's a lot of obscurity</i>

865
00:42:13.097 --> 00:42:16.556
<i>I'm not inclined to
resign to maturity</i>

866
00:42:16.634 --> 00:42:19.798
<i>If it's all right then
you're all wrong</i>

867
00:42:19.871 --> 00:42:23.501
<i>But why bounce around
to the same damn song?</i>

868
00:42:24.642 --> 00:42:28.704
<i>You'd rather run
when you can't crawl</i>

869
00:42:30.848 --> 00:42:34.307
<i>I know. you know That
I'm not telling the truth</i>

870
00:42:34.385 --> 00:42:37.446
<i>I know. you know They
just don't have any proof</i>

871
00:42:37.522 --> 00:42:40.686
<i>Embrace the deception
Learn how to bend</i>

872
00:42:40.758 --> 00:42:44.752
<i>Your worst inhibitions tend
to psych you out in the end</i>

873
00:42:44.829 --> 00:42:46.525
<i>I know. you know</i>

874
00:42:48.433 --> 00:42:50.061
<i>I know. you know</i>
